definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate + H2O -eq- 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate + H(2)O -eq- 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1D-myo-inositol 1,4-bisphosphate + H2O -eq- 1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate + phosphate.

Catalysis of the reactions -  D-myo-inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate + H2O -eq- myo-inositol 1,4-bisphosphate + phosphate, and 1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4,5-tetrakisphosphate + H2O -eq- 1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4-trisphosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  myo-inositol hexakisphosphate + H2O -eq- myo-inositol pentakisphosphate (mixed isomers) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  iodide + hydrogen peroxide -eq- iodine + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  isocitrate + acceptor -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + CO2 + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  isocitrate + NAD+ -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + CO2 + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  isocitrate + NADP+ -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + CO2 + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  isocitrate -eq- glyoxylate + succinate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- dimethylallyl diphosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  methyl (2E,6E)-(10R,11S)-10,11-epoxy-3,7,11-trimethyltrideca-2,6-dienoate + H2O -eq- (2E,6E)-(10R,11S)-10,11-epoxy-3,7,11-trimethyltrideca-2,6-dienoate + methanol. A carboxylesterase that hydrolyzes the ester linkage of juvenile hormone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + D-fructose -eq- ADP + D-fructose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-2,3-dihydroxy-3-methylbutanoate + NADP+ -eq- (S)-2-hydroxy-2-methyl-3-oxobutanoate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-phospho-D-gluconate -eq- 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-6-phospho-D-gluconate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  lactate + NAD+ -eq- H+ + NADH + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-lactate + 2 ferricytochrome c -eq- pyruvate + 2 ferrocytochrome c.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-lactate + NAD+ -eq- pyruvate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-lactate + 2 ferricytochrome c -eq- pyruvate + 2 ferrocytochrome c.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-galactose + D-glucose -eq- UDP + lactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-S-lactoylglutathione -eq- glutathione + methylglyoxal.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(2)O + leukotriene A(4) -eq- leukotriene B(4).
Catalysis of the reaction -  leukotriene C(4) -eq- glutathione + leukotriene A(4).
Catalysis of the reaction -  triacylglycerol + H2O -eq- diacylglycerol + a carboxylate, where the triacylglycerol is part of a lipoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + ETF -eq- 2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + reduced ETF.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a long-chain carboxylic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + an acyl-CoA -  a long-chain fatty acid is a fatty acid with a chain length between C13 and C22.

label.value: lysine N-acetyltransferase activity, acting on acetyl phosphate as donor

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl phosphate + L-lysine -eq- phosphate + N6-acetyl-L-lysine.
Catalysis of the oxidative decarboxylation of malate with the concomitant production of pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-malate + NAD+ -eq- pyruvate + CO2 + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-malate + NADP+ -eq- pyruvate + CO2 + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + glyoxylate + H(2)O -eq- (S)-malate + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-D-mannose 1-phosphate + GTP -eq- diphosphate + GDP-alpha-D-mannose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-mannose 6-phosphate -eq- D-fructose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,10-methenyltetrahydrofolate + H2O -eq- 10-formyltetrahydrofolate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-methionine + H2O -eq- phosphate + diphosphate + S-adenosyl-L-methionine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  10-formyltetrahydrofolate + L-methionyl-tRNA + H2O -eq- tetrahydrofolate + N-formylmethionyl-tRNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + phospholipid olefinic fatty acid -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + phospholipid methylene fatty acid.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + G(5')pppR-RNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + m7G(5')pppR-RNA. m7G(5')pppR-RNA is mRNA containing an N7-methylguanine cap -  R may be guanosine or adenosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + m7G(5')pppR-RNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + m7G(5')pppRm-RNA. R may be guanosine or adenosine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + (5')pp-Pur-mRNA -eq- diphosphate + G(5')ppp-Pur-mRNA -  G(5')ppp-Pur-mRNA is mRNA containing a guanosine residue linked 5' through three phosphates to the 5' position of the terminal residue.

Catalysis of the reaction -  5-methyltetrahydrofolate + NAD(P)+ -eq- 5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl-CoA -eq- trans-3-methylglutaconyl-CoA + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-methyl-3-oxopropanoate + CoA + NAD+ -eq- propanoyl-CoA + CO2 + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-2-methyl-3-oxopropanoyl-CoA -eq- propanoyl-CoA + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-methylmalonyl-CoA -eq- (S)-methylmalonyl-CoA.
